<review>Came here with my husband and 3 year old ASD son.  The wait wasn't bad on a Saturday morning.  We were seated, greeted with a smile, offered drinks, and made our order quickly.  Food came out and it was delicious!  My son is a picky eat and he ate happily ate his smiley face pancake with banana and sausage and egg.  My waffle was delicious.  The bacon is super yummy and a thicker cut.  My son even stole bacon off my plate.  The jam that comes with toast is perfect - not too sweet.  My husband loved his blueberry french toast.  The service was fabulous, food delicious, and you can't ask for much more from a restaurant.<//review>< pics>

< Review>
It was my 1st time visiting and I was pleasantly surprised. The restaurant is connected through a quaint little gift shop. The wait wasn't long for a Saturday morning (10ish) We browswd through the store filled with cute gift ideas of all kinds from tea sets to baby gifts. The restaurant atmosphere was very welcoming. It felt like being at home, well except you don't have to do the cooking or cleaning. Our server was amazing, she was very friendly and helpful. The fresh squeezed orange juice was to die for. I ordered the Viking combo: French toast with eggs, bacon and sausage with a side of Country Home Fries. I would definitely recommend  the potatoes, the flavors were amazing. Lastly we shared an Aebleskiver, which was very yummy. Overall it was definitely a great experience and will be returning again every chance I get.<//Review>

<name>LouEllen Trevino</name>< date>
1541533205465< /date>
<rating>1< /rating>< text>
I hadn't been to Valhalla for years. Now I remember why. I ordered bacon and eggs. My medium eggs were fried to a golden brown, so crispy you could not cut them. I sent them back, but the replacement eggs weren't much better. I asked for crispy bacon that came burned. I had coffee, and had to ask for a refill. Our server Carolyn (I think that was her name) had passed our table twice with the coffee pot and never offered a refill. I happened to look in my cup after I had drank most of it, and realized the cup must have been dirty to start with as white gunk was floating around in it. Yuck! The server was very pleasant, but not on top of her game. Our abelskivers were way over done. However, my husband's ham slice was very tasty. Just a sad experience. Won't be going back.<//text>

<UserId.>115360496187310813108<//UserId.>< name>
Cosme Woodard</name>
<time>1559037442512< /time><Rating>5</Rating>< Text>
I adore this place.  The gift shop has the classiest, girliest items, and I keep buying jewelry for myself and for gifts for other women there.  Though, I do intend on getting myself a pink tea set from there one of these days.  The restaurant part of it...is amazing!  I like the Valhalla Breakfast Special, which consists of two eggs (well-cooked for me), 2 aebelskivers, and medisterpolse (homemade Danish sausage).  Really huge portions and really delicious, authentic, home-made food.  An absolute treat.  Also, the owner, Kim, is always so kind when I happen to run into her, when she's not cooking up a storm in the back...great service, interesting decor, and wonderful food.  I'm a tried-and-true kind of a girl, so I plan on sticking with the Valhalla Breakfast special for a long time, but I do want to try the Belgian waffles there!!!</Text>

<name>Arman Goshtasbe</name><user_id>117728974531965252394< /user_id>< text>
A gem of a place in downtown Visalia. Great food, even if you are a vegetarian or vegan. If you are a T Rex you will definitely love it. Tons of choices for meat eaters.

The gift shop is cool too. Reminds me a little of Cracker Barrel restaurant in that sense. For those of you who are down with our Southern family and know what Cracker Barrel even is.

My point is, this place is definitely worth a visit if you are an out-of-towner and definitely worth a visit if you are an in-towner.

Tell them this google review sent you. You won't get a discount, nor will I get anything, but it's something different to say rather than the typical standard ole "Hi, I'd like a table for 5 please"

If you're not saying HI or PLEASE to begin with... you know what... never-mind... not going to get preachy. This review is not the place.

Long story short, go check this place out. Worth a visit. Even if you are a brontosaurus like me.</text>

I came here for breakfast with my husband at the time, a Mexican man with a thick beard whose ethnicity was vague. It was the day after the Paris shooting. We were waiting in line and the host, an older white man, said to the veteran in front of us that he might have to go back to war. Then he stared down my husband, looked him in the eye, and said "that's what happens when you let just anyone in." We were dumbfounded and left immediately. I was looking forward to local Swedish food, but I would rather drive to Kingsburg for Swedish food than give Valhalla my business.<//review>

< review>
The iced coffee is like no other I've had before. It's rich and creamy and ends on a familiar and not unpleasant bitter note.

If you want to try the Asian sandwich side of the menu, but don't know where to start the #4 grilled chicken is a great option. Chicken has a slight teriyaki flavor going on that's balanced by the crunchy pickled veggies, jalapeÃ±o, onions, and cilantro. Yum all around.

And I finally tried the macaroons! There was no label so a blind choice turned out to be vanilla. So light and the filling very creamy.

All in all worth a trip for a light and energizing lunch.<//review>

<rate>5<//rate><review>We purchased a well taken care of preowned class A motorhome from Conejo RV Sales. Upon taking delivery I had a few questions. Just before departing Vegas I noticed a small puddle of fuel at the back of the coach. I called and spoke with Jim, who had contacted Rick, the owner, and from my description of the issue, decdied it was something to do with the fuel line to the generator. I was advised NOT to run the generator and to bring it in for service the first opportunity possible. We drove to LA without running the generator only to discover we still were leaking fuel. I called Jim again and he didn't hesitate to give me Rick's number directly. The OWNER of the company gladly took my call, on a Sunday evening, his only day off, discussed with me the issue and determined I needed a new fuel pump. He told me to have it towed to the shop when our vacation was over and he'd take care of the problem. Monday morning the fuel pump was ordered and expedited to the shop. When I tried to get my refund I was told by the new manager that since I signed the document I was suppose to commit to the YEAR OF TRAINING. Apparently my wife and I weren't just fraudulently lured to a "month TRIAL", we were lured AND STILL ARE tied down to a YEAR CONTRACT. Over 1,000$ down the drain.

While I do want to make one thing clear, the three trainers who took turns training us were awesome, we have nothing but good things to say about them, our overall experience with the actual company was awful. The fact you can fire a manager for engaging in fraud, luring people like my wife and I to $1,000 dollar services, and then telling me because my signature is on the document that I can't cancel it is literally the definition of fraud. It's a breach of contract if I know any. Once more, the trainers were amazing and i'd recommend them to the world, but my issue is to corporate, or whoever runs the show in this place.

<Text>Perfect location, friendly staff, neat facility with a cardio cinema and steam room! Parking is plenty around the building.

I signed up in October of 2019 since I moved to Murrieta and have since tried multiple group classes including Barr, Bodypump, pilates, yoga and more along with PT with Doulla. Variety of group classes keeps me engaged and having fun while exercising! As for PT, it was my first experience training with a trainer and I can't say enough good things about my trainer Doulla - she went through a thorough introductory session to identify the areas I needed to focus on and the core of my challenge, which is the hip tendonitis and customized a workout routine that works perfect for a weighlift beginner like myself, while reducing further injury. With her, I consider myself in great hands to get fitter and overcome injuries!

Also, I am grategul to Yusef for a great complementary welcome workout - the session was so much more than what I expected and it was what prompted me to sign up for the PT right away.

Overall, I love the gym. The only thing I hope for is maybe a bigger and cleaner restroom. The locker room is rather small and the showers are limited-only 3 for such a huge gym. Oh well, considering the services they provide and its price, it's a small problem that wouldn't deter me from continuing to enjoy this gym. I'd avoid the hours between 5 to 8 pm on weekdays if wants to avoid the crowds.< /Text><user_id>106579711042684843315<//user_id>< time>

As for the rude staff, I will say that when I first signed up, there was one girl at the front desk that seemed to be bothered by anyone that came in the door, thankfully she's gone. but every morning I go in (usually around 5am), I'm always greeted by Lance (who knows my name) and I always get a "have a great workout" on my way in. When leaving, I always get the "have a great day!" This is a fairly small gym in comparison to the 24hr in Temecula and yes, its gets busy (I used to go at night), but if you can change your routine slightly, problem solved. Every morning there is free equipment to use, the staff is helpful and happy to answer questions. There is one guy that seems to think he's God's gift, but you know what... not everyone you come across in life is pleasant, so I know if I want to pay for a trainer, it AIN'T gonna be him! LOL. On the fee side, I had them double bill me once due to a change over in their system. Called customer service and problem solved. Instead of billing me for the following month, they applied the double payment to the next month, OH, they also offered me a refund of the extra billing too?< /text>< resp>

< review>
I'm very shock reading some of these reviews,  our family loves going to EOS Murrieta. All of us have been going since January 2016, we have never seen any rude staff act unprofessional.  They have always been very nice from the day we started,  love Jordan always very pleasant and Cutter is the guy to go to when things aren't working or need attention they always ask how things are going never had an issue with none of them. One thing that I would love to put out there is, thanking my Trainer Sean Shannon who was assigned to me when I started in January. He is an amazing trainer and a great motivator, never seen a trainer who goes above and beyond for his clients. Sean actually cares about his clients, and checks on you when your sick or injured to see how your feeling. Now this is a trainer who really loves what he is doing and very knowledgeable on what he is doing, when it comes to your diet and training. When I started training in January 2016 with Sean, because of his motivation, diet and training never giving up on me I have lost over 45lbs and I feel amazing. Being a mom and turning 50 years old, after having 3 kids I feel good and more confident in myself.  I wanted to say thank you Sean for everything, you are an awesome trainer. Thank you EOS you have made me believe in a gym again, also thank you to Sean's wife Edele she is amazing. Thank youI absolutely love EOS Murrieta, I started working out in January 2016. My trainer Sean goes above and beyond, when taking care of his clients. He is very considered and motivating when it comes to your diet and training, he checks on u when your unable to make it to the gym due to an injury or illness. Thanks to his motivation, diet and training I have lost over 45lbs since January 2016. And I wanted to thank him for never giving up on me, Sean you are an amazing trainer ..
Now from reading several reviews on Facebook and Google, and don't get me wrong everybody is entitled to their own opinion. But come on people seriously, let me just throw it out there since some of these things the staff can't. So I will speak for them...
*1 this is a gym where u go to workout at, relax or let of some steam or stress before or after work. It's not a dating neither a pick up place or for people to hog equipment while they are talking on the phone. It's called common courtesy and respect for others.
*2 once again this is a gym with members going in and out 24/7 best rates than everywhere else and people still complain about the smallest things. It's impossible to maintain a gym  clean 24/7, I have yet to see any gym that way so it's understandable.. Times that we have been going, there is always a cleaning crew in the bathrooms or vacuuming the gym and most times it's so crowded so they do the best they can. If the cleaning crew would interrupt your training cause there is some trash, you people would complain about that too. There is no win, win in all this..
*3 If you see trash laying around by equipment or empty water bottles guess what people, that is your trash you left there cause you guys where to lazy to put it in the trash.This is a gym not your personal maid service to pick up after you, your the ones who brought it in and you should be responsible for throwing your own trash away in the trash cans provide for you..
*4 There are always going to be issues no matter where you go, you can't please everyone. And being prior members of 24hr fitness, don't even get me started.
Our family loves coming to EOS Murrieta and we are so happy that we made the change, hands down to all of you. Specially my trainer Sean Shannon thank you.< /review>

< Time>
1567103028058< /Time>
<Rate>5</Rate>< Review>
Disclaimer: I've known Jeff Harris (Owner of Advanced Automotive) for quite some time now.  He is one of the most trustworthy, honest, high integrity person I've ever met so naturally when he bought Advanced Automative several years ago I figured I'd give it a try.  My experience was great.  No complaints.

Then latter on when I needed to get a car repair I went there one day late in the afternoon and they were a little busy so I decided to go somewhere else bc it was somewhat urgent.  Long story short It's been probably about 2 years since I've been.

Disclaimer #2: I'm not good with cars at all!  I know nothing about them and could very easily get taken advantage of.  For that reason (and the fact that I'm lazy and probably not as responsible as I should be :)) I had a LOT of deferred maintenance with my truck.  But it wasn't until I was going down a hill with my son and had to stop at a red light and wasn't sure if I would be able to that I decided the situation was URGENT and I needed to take my vehicle in or I would be putting myself and family in danger each time we went anywhere.

However in the back of my mind I thought oh man I'm going to be taken advantage of bc I have no idea what I'm doing.  Then I remembered Jeff's shop and thought well since I know Jeff to be such a stand up guy I imagine his shop is ran by stand up people and he's taught them how he wants things done.

Having that been said I still figured they would tell me EVERYTHING needed to be done and it was ALL urgent!  And even though they probably could have done that justifiable and been pretty accurate I just didn't like that I wouldn't know.

But I had no choice to take it in to at least get the breaks fixed so I went for it.  They got be in quickly.  I called ahead of time and Chrissy was very nice as well as when I showed up.

Justin (great name) took at look at my vehicle, and I received a report stating everything that was fine with my car, somethings that they recommended and then a couple of things that were urgent.

The ONLY things that they said were urgent was the breaks, which I knew was true.  To my huge surprise the other things they told me weren't an emergency but they recommended them but at no time did I feel like I was being manipulated or taken advantage of.  But felt like they were looking after me and just giving the pure facts.  There were a couple of items I had done recently and none of them came up on the recommended list.  A couple of the items that came up I asked about and I never felt like I was being high pressure sold but just educated.  It felt like I had someone who was just there to give me the information and help me understand instead of take advantage of my ignorance.

I looked up a coupe of the recommended items on the list and sure enough each time the cost I found online was always higher than what they quoted me.

Since I knew I could trust them I decided to just move forward with all of the recommended items and I feel like I have a new truck and my family is safe.  And my wife is proud of me for being a man and getting the truck fixed! :) even though I did a lot of work.  They got me my vehicle back that same day and even stayed a little late until I came to pick it up.

I would HIGHLY recommend Advanced Automative to anyone who is looking for a shop they can rely on with trustworthy good people who are working behind the desk, under the hood and behind the scene to make sure your vehicle and family are taken care of.<//Review>

< Name>
Don Clouser<//Name>
<date>1611036966996</date><gmapID>0x8082d886566db707:0xd2f53e72fb6d092< /gmapID>< review>

I recently purchased a new Toyota Camry and was fortunate to work with two excellent Chuck Patterson representatives. My initial contacts were online with Michelle Carroll. < text>
I purchased a used 2013 Prius in February 2016 with under 50000 miles. About 6 months into it the Bluetooth began cutting out and disconnecting the phones thus not being legal to comply with the California hands free law. Also it does not allow music to be streamed from a laptop or other device. It was somewhat intermittent and when I took it in and had it checked out it was working and there was nothing they could do until it was out when I brought it in. A few weeks later when driving nearby to the selling dealer it went out, had the Toyota service technician set in the car and he said the Bluetooth portion was indeed defective. when they called I was told that the "Cellular Telephone" was the only part of the radio that was not covered by our $2700+ warranty. So unless another function failed there was nothing they could do. FYI upon purchase I remember asking the finance person if the radio and Bluetooth was covered, and was told "everything except wear and tear items are covered bumper to bumper". I believe I was misled by the selling dealer and they were not willing to "JUST MAKE IT RIGHT" I would not be so upset except I asked this specific question beforehand, "does the warranty cover the radio and the Bluetooth" Had they told us this in the first place it very well may had swayed my extended warranty purchase. Not happy with Chuck Patterson Toyota of Chico, Ca</text>

<Time>1413839219834< /Time>< text>
We contacted CP to purchase our 1st straight from the lot, new car. We decided to buy on Labor Day weekend because of the great sales. When we showed up around 5:00pm, Brad Marr greeted us and we sat down for a few min. He introduced us to Dallas, we told him we wanted to drive the Corolla LE, the Camry and the Prius, and we were off for some test drives. We had a great time testing out the different vehicles, and settled on the Corolla. There really was no haggling on the price as we did our homework prior to the day and new the prices were fair already with all of the incentives and bonuses and such. After realizing that the 2015 Corolla's did not have the 0% apr, we settled on the 2014. The paperwork was drawn up in approx. 15 min and we signed in about 5 minutes, it took Dallas longer to program my wifes' cell phone to the blue-tooth in the car than it did to do the paperwork (and he did it pretty quick), that was awesome. All around great bunch of guys/gals at Chuck Patterson and can't wait to buy my 1st New truck from them. Brad was instrumental in the sale of this vehicle by making my wife comfortable (not having ever bought a New car) and Dallas did a great job as well. From the sales Manager to the salesman to the young lady in financing, absolutely great experience. A+ in my book.....

Thank you Chuck Patterson Toyota/Scion/Dodge of Chico.< /text>

I told them I was going to call Chuck Patterson, because no way should I have to pay for something that they broke. So they filled the tire, explained to me that the tire would just start slowly seeping air again, and the light would come back on soon.
